dsDescriptionValue.value:
This unit presented Rs with a screen on which there were three boxes, along with letters and numbers which moved on the screen, and at the top of the screen an 'L' or an 'N'. The Rs task was to move either letters (if L was at the top of the screen) or numbers (if N was at the top) into the boxes by typing the letter or number and pressing the return key. The dependent variables of interest were the percentage of possible opportunities to score in which R does move the appropriate digit into a box, the percentage of possible opportunities which are missed, and the number of incorrect moves (ie moving a letter when the N is at the top of the screen or vice-versa, or moving a digit which was not out of a box). The major independent variable in this design was group size. Each R worked in four group size conditions in one of four orders. the sequence was completed once.

IN CAPS/85 it was completed twice. Other differences between the CAPS/85 and 86 versions was no anon/team manipulation in 86 and the addition of a departmental condition in 86.

See codebook for additional information
